==English==
'''deadrise'''
===Noun===
<!--{{wikipedia}} uncomment if you know there is a Wikipedia article-->
# ((nautical))The angle between a horizontal line drawn from the [[keel]] and
the angle of the [[garboard]] and it's attachment to the [[keel]]. Or 
The very term deadrise means a straight rise of bottom or floor
extended out from the side of the [[keel]] at whatever angle of rise a
particular boat design calls for.

